<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Journal Prompts</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #D2B48C; /* Corkboard color */
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            height: 100vh;
        }

        .container {
            width: 90%;
            max-width: 1200px;
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(200px, 1fr));
            gap: 20px;
        }

        .sticky-note {
            background-color: #FFFACD; /* Sticky note yellow */
            padding: 20px;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
            border: 2px solid #FFD700; /* Golden border for a sticky note feel */
            border-radius: 8px;
            position: relative;
            cursor: pointer;
            transition: transform 0.2s ease;
            overflow: hidden;
        }

        .sticky-note:hover {
            transform: scale(1.05);
        }

        .sticky-note.expanded {
            grid-column: span 2;
            grid-row: span 2;
        }

        .sticky-note-header {
            font-weight: bold;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
            color: #333;
            font-size: 1.2rem;
        }

        .sticky-note-content {
            max-height: 80px;
            overflow: hidden;
            transition: max-height 0.3s ease;
            font-size: 1rem;
        }

        .sticky-note.expanded .sticky-note-content {
            max-height: 400px;
        }

        .toggle-button {
            position: absolute;
            bottom: 10px;
            right: 10px;
            background-color: #F0E68C; /* Button color to match sticky note */
            border: none;
            padding: 5px 10px;
            border-radius: 5px;
            cursor: pointer;
        }

    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <div class="container">
        <!-- Example journal prompt sticky notes -->
        <div class="sticky-note" id="note-1" onclick="toggleExpand(1)">
            <div class="sticky-note-header">What are you grateful for today?</div>
            <div class="sticky-note-content">Today, I’m grateful for the support of my friends and family who helped me through a difficult week...</div>
            <button class="toggle-button">Expand</button>
        </div>
        <div class="sticky-note" id="note-2" onclick="toggleExpand(2)">
            <div class="sticky-note-header">What is your biggest goal right now?</div>
            <div class="sticky-note-content">My biggest goal is to finish my personal project by the end of the month. It’s been a challenging journey...</div>
            <button class="toggle-button">Expand</button>
        </div>
        <div class="sticky-note" id="note-3" onclick="toggleExpand(3)">
            <div class="sticky-note-header">What made you smile today?</div>
            <div class="sticky-note-content">I smiled when I saw my dog run excitedly to greet me as I came home. It’s the small moments...</div>
            <button class="toggle-button">Expand</button>
        </div>
        <div class="sticky-note" id="note-4" onclick="toggleExpand(4)">
            <div class="sticky-note-header">Describe a challenge you're facing.</div>
            <div class="sticky-note-content">I’m facing a challenge at work with a tight deadline for an important project. It’s been tough managing the stress, but...</div>
            <button class="toggle-button">Expand</button>
        </div>
        <div class="sticky-note" id="note-5" onclick="toggleExpand(5)">
            <div class="sticky-note-header">How do you feel right now?</div>
            <div class="sticky-note-content">Right now, I feel a mix of excitement and nervousness as I look ahead at what’s coming next in my career...</div>
            <button class="toggle-button">Expand</button>
        </div>
    </div>

    <script>
        function toggleExpand(index) {
            var note = document.getElementById('note-' + index);
            note.classList.toggle('expanded');
        }
    </script>

</body>
</html>

